value:
Yes, the Company has the following policies in place to avoid / manage the conflict of interest involving members of the Board:
1. Policy on Anti-Bribery and Anti-Corruption;
2. Code of Conduct for Board Members and Senior Management Personnel;
3. Code of conduct for prevention of Insider Trading;
4. Code of Practices and Procedures for disclosure of Unpublished Price Sensitive Information;
5. Whistle Blower Policy;
6. Policy for Materiality of Event;
7. Policy on Related Party Transaction.
